# Linting & Formatting

This project uses **ESLint + Oxlint** only. No Prettier.

## Tooling

- Config: `eslint.config.mjs` using `@nuxt/eslint-config` + `eslint-plugin-oxlint` + `eslint-plugin-tailwindcss`.
- Formatting is handled entirely via `@stylistic/eslint-plugin` (bundled in `@nuxt/eslint-config`).
- Run: `pnpm lint` to check, `pnpm lint:fix` to auto-fix.

## Style Rules (enforced by ESLint)

| Rule | Value |
|---|---|
| Indent | **tabs** |
| Quotes | **double** |
| Semicolons | **required** |
| Line endings | LF |

```ts
// ✅ CORRECT
const message = "Hello world";

// ❌ WRONG (single quotes, no semi, spaces)
const message = 'Hello world'
```

## Padding Lines

ESLint enforces blank lines between variable declarations and other statements:

```ts
const userId = route.params.id;
const userData = await fetchUser(userId);

// blank line required before return
return userData;
```

## Pre-commit

`lint-staged` via Husky runs on every commit. Never commit code that fails `pnpm lint`.

## Tailwind Class Sorting

Tailwind class linting is enabled via `eslint-plugin-tailwindcss`. Custom design tokens and shadcn patterns are allowed (`tailwindcss/no-custom-classname` is off). Always use `cn()` for conditional class merging.
